worksforme: <p>
You should use
</p>
<pre class="wiki">&lt;ol&gt;
    &lt;?php wp_list_bookmarks(); ?&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
</pre><p>
or
</p>
<pre class="wiki">&lt;ul&gt;
    &lt;?php wp_list_bookmarks(); ?&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</pre><p>
It's the same as for wp_list_comments() and wp_list_categories(). See also the codex for examples.
</p>

wontfix: <p>
Should others try to achive the same, with 3.1 it's possible to do it with a filter like this:
</p>
<pre class="wiki">function cba_get_comment_list_by_user($clauses) {
	if (is_admin()) {
		global $user_ID, $wpdb;
		$clauses['join'] = ", cba_posts";
		$clauses['where'] .= " AND ".$wpdb-&gt;prefix."posts.post_author = ".$user_ID." AND ".$wpdb-&gt;prefix."comments.comment_post_ID = ".$wpdb-&gt;prefix."posts.ID";
	};
	return $clauses;
};
add_filter('comments_clauses', 'cba_get_comment_list_by_user');
</pre><p>
Closing the ticket.
</p>
